# Email Ingest — First-Time Setup

Setting up email ingest is the most involved part of the personal intelligence kit. This guide walks you through it for Gmail (most common), with notes for other providers.

## 1. Install tools

**macOS:**
```bash
brew install isync notmuch
```

**Linux:**
```bash
apt install isync notmuch
```

## 2. Generate an app-specific password (Gmail)

Normal Gmail passwords don't work with IMAP. Generate an app password:

1. Visit https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
2. Create a new app password for "Mail" → "Mac"
3. Copy the 16-character password (you won't see it again)

## 3. Store credentials securely

**macOS (Keychain):**
```bash
security add-internet-password \
  -s imap.gmail.com \
  -a YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com \
  -w
# (paste the app password when prompted)
```

**Linux (gpg):**
```bash
echo "YOUR_APP_PASSWORD" | gpg --encrypt -r YOUR_GPG_ID > ~/.email-password.gpg
```

## 4. Configure `~/.mbsyncrc`

Create `~/.mbsyncrc` with this template:

```ini
# ============================================================
# Gmail account for {{ owner_name }}
# ============================================================

IMAPAccount gmail
Host imap.gmail.com
User YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com
# macOS keychain:
PassCmd "security find-internet-password -s imap.gmail.com -a YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com -w"
# Linux gpg alternative:
# PassCmd "gpg --decrypt ~/.email-password.gpg"
TLSType IMAPS
AuthMechs LOGIN

IMAPStore gmail-remote
Account gmail

MaildirStore gmail-local
Subfolders Verbatim
Path {{ email_path }}/
Inbox {{ email_path }}/Inbox

Channel gmail
Far :gmail-remote:
Near :gmail-local:
Patterns "INBOX" "[Gmail]/Sent Mail" "[Gmail]/All Mail"
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

# IMPORTANT: Limit initial sync to the most recent 1000 messages.
# Remove or increase this once you're comfortable.
MaxMessages 1000
```

Replace `YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com` with your address throughout.

## 5. Run the first sync

```bash
mkdir -p {{ email_path }}
mbsync -a
```

This downloads the most recent 1000 messages to `{{ email_path }}`. It may take several minutes.

## 6. Initialize notmuch

```bash
notmuch setup
```

Interactive prompts will ask:
- **Your name:** `{{ owner_name }}`
- **Primary email:** your address
- **Database path:** `{{ email_path }}` (must match mbsync Path)

Then index the messages:

```bash
notmuch new
```

## 7. Verify

```bash
notmuch count 'date:today..'
notmuch search --limit=5 'date:7d..'
```

Both should return results.

## Ongoing Sync

Running `data-sync` (or this skill directly) will re-run `mbsync -a && notmuch new`. Safe to run as often as you like — it's incremental.

## Other Providers

- **Fastmail / iCloud / custom IMAP:** Use their IMAP host/port (`imap.fastmail.com:993`, `imap.mail.me.com:993`, etc.) and an app-specific password.
- **Multiple accounts:** Add additional `IMAPAccount`/`Channel` blocks to `~/.mbsyncrc`.

## Removing the MaxMessages limit

Once you're comfortable and want full history, edit `~/.mbsyncrc` and comment out:
```ini
# MaxMessages 1000
```
Then re-run `mbsync -a`. The next sync will pull older mail.
